messages.message:

Already on 'master'

Please move or remove them before you switch branches.

fatal: Could not detach HEAD

Already on 'master'

I didn't know so many people used vscode settings, I may change this and just put creating your own vscode settings file (that's git ignored) part of onboarding instructions for frontend

this or `subl .vscode/settings.json` both don’t work
```(venv3) ➜  data-api-utils git:(master) ✗ git rm --cached .vscode/settings.json
fatal: pathspec '.vscode/settings.json' did not match any files```
and `.vscode/` is in the gitignore file
the full path from wherever i am should be `.vscode/settings.json` if it just shows up like that?
can you try just mv-ing it somewhere else temporarily?
or does it not exist at all? haha alternatively you can use vim :wink:
Hmm part of my change was to remove .vscode/settings.json from gitignore, so it shouldn't be in there anymore
The .vscode directory is in the root `instabase` directory
I think I can’t pull master because of this
thanks @Jessica think I got rid of it
